def is_prime(n):
    if n <= 1:
        return False
    elif n <= 3:
        return True
    elif n % 2 == 0 or n % 3 == 0:
        return False
    i = 5
    while i * i <= n:
        if n % i == 0 or n % (i + 2) == 0:
            return False
        i += 6
    return True
```

This function works by checking divisibility starting from 2 up to the square root of the number. It skips even numbers after checking for 2, and checks pairs of potential factors that differ by 2 (i.e., 3 and 5, 7 and 9, etc.) to further improve efficiency.

The function returns True if the number is prime and False otherwise.

